    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan:\n\n## Summary\n\nAdding `Bun.INI` with `parse` and `stringify` requires touching **6 files** (1 new, 5 modified) following the exact same pattern used by `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.YAML`, etc.\n\n### File to Create\n- **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — The object with `create()`, `parse()`, and `stringify()`\n  - `parse` reuses the existing `ini.Parser` from `src/ini.zig` (the same code that `IniTestingAPIs.parse` uses — Bun's own Zig implementation, not the npm INI parser)\n  - `stringify` is written from scratch: flat key=value pairs first, then nested objects as `[section]` blocks, arrays as `key[] = element` lines\n\n### Files to Modify\n1. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Register `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — 3 small additions: lazy prop constant, `@export` in `exportAll()`, getter function, and import alias\n3. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI) \\` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n4. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the `bunObjectTable`\n5. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI { parse(input: string): object; stringify(value: object): string; }`\n\n### Test\n- `test/js/bun/ini/bun_ini_public_api.test.ts` — spawn tests for parse, stringify, round-trips, sections, arrays, and comments",
